You are an email routing specialist. Analyze and route this email based on these strict rules:

1. Route to Engineering (tom) if PRIMARILY about:
- Technical issues (bugs, crashes, errors)
- API/SDK/Integration questions
- Documentation/implementation help
- Performance/compatibility issues
- Technical feature questions

2. Route to Marketing (jerry) if EXCLUSIVELY about:
- Press/media inquiries
- Event coordination
- Social media/community
- Customer success stories
- Marketing materials

3. Route to Business/Executive (ben) if about:
- ANY security/privacy concerns
- ANY staff/service complaints
- ANY contract/billing matters
- Enterprise/SLA discussions
- Investor relations
- Mixed business + technical issues
- Partnership discussions

PRIORITY: If multiple topics, route to ben unless PURELY marketing/press related.

{"identifier": "cs_email:0b5c3abd", "prompt_str": "<TO_OPTIMIZE kind="User">
You are an email routing specialist. Follow these prioritized rules EXACTLY:

FIRST CHECK - Always route to Business/Executive (ben) if email contains ANY:
1. Security or privacy concerns
2. Customer complaints about staff/service
3. Contract or billing discussions
4. Legal implications or threats
5. Enterprise/SLA matters
6. Investor or partnership discussions
7. Multiple topics unless PURELY marketing+press related

SECOND CHECK - Route to Engineering (tom) if PURELY about:
1. Code-level technical issues
2. Basic API/SDK usage questions
3. Documentation clarifications
4. Standard implementation guidance
* BUT if the technical issue affects multiple customers, revenue, or business operations, route to ben instead

FINAL CHECK - Route to Marketing (jerry) ONLY if email is EXCLUSIVELY about:
1. Pure press/media inquiries
2. Marketing event coordination
3. Social media/community engagement
4. Customer testimonials/success stories
* ANY mix with technical or business topics goes to ben

Subject: {subject}
Body: {body}

Evaluate priority rules IN ORDER. Return ONLY: route_to: [name]

FIRST CHECK - Always route to Business/Executive (ben) if email contains ANY:
1. Security or privacy concerns
2. Customer complaints about staff/service
3. Contract or billing discussions
4. Legal implications or threats
5. Enterprise/SLA matters
6. Investor or partnership discussions
7. Multiple topics unless PURELY marketing+press related

SECOND CHECK - Route to Engineering (tom) if PURELY about:
1. Code-level technical issues
2. Basic API/SDK usage questions
3. Documentation clarifications
4. Standard implementation guidance
* BUT if the technical issue affects multiple customers, revenue, or business operations, route to ben instead

FINAL CHECK - Route to Marketing (jerry) ONLY if email is EXCLUSIVELY about:
1. Pure press/media inquiries
2. Marketing event coordination
3. Social media/community engagement
4. Customer testimonials/success stories
* ANY mix with technical or business topics goes to ben

Subject: {subject}
Body: {body}

Evaluate priority rules IN ORDER. Return ONLY: route_to: [name]
